  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the different grade levels and titles at Deloitte Consulting US?",
  "response": "Deloitte Consulting US, like many other consulting firms, has a hierarchical structure with various grade levels and titles. The specific titles and levels may vary slightly depending on the specific service line or practice within Deloitte Consulting. Here is a general overview of the grade levels and titles at Deloitte Consulting US:\n\n1. **Analyst/Consultant**\n   - **Grade Level:** Entry-level\n   - **Titles:** Analyst, Consultant\n   - **Description:** This is typically the starting point for new hires, often recent graduates. They work under the supervision of more experienced team members, contributing to project execution and client deliverables.\n\n2. **Senior Consultant**\n   - **Grade Level:** Mid-level\n   - **Title:** Senior Consultant\n   - **Description:** At this level, individuals have gained some experience and are capable of taking on more responsibility. They often lead smaller workstreams within projects and mentor junior staff.\n\n3. **Manager**\n   - **Grade Level:** Mid-to-senior level\n   - **Title:** Manager\n   - **Description:** Managers are responsible for leading project teams, managing client relationships, and ensuring the successful delivery of projects. They play a key role in business development and client engagement.\n\n4. **Senior Manager**\n   - **Grade Level:** Senior level\n   - **Title:** Senior Manager\n   - **Description:** Senior Managers have significant experience and often lead larger, more complex projects. They are involved in strategic planning, client relationship management, and may start to take on firm leadership roles.\n\n5. **Director**\n   - **Grade Level:** Senior leadership\n   - **Title:** Director\n   - **Description:** Directors are responsible for overseeing multiple projects and client relationships. They contribute to the firm's growth strategy, lead business development efforts, and play a significant role in shaping the firm's offerings.\n\n6. **Principal**\n   - **Grade Level:** Executive level\n   - **Title:** Principal\n   - **Description:** Principals are senior leaders within the firm, often responsible for a specific practice or service line. They have a significant impact on the firm's strategic direction, client relationships, and overall growth.\n\n7. **Managing Director/Partner**\n   - **Grade Level:** Top executive level\n   - **Titles:** Managing Director, Partner\n   - **Description:** Managing Directors and Partners are at the top of the organizational hierarchy. They are responsible for the overall leadership of the firm, driving strategic initiatives, and maintaining key client relationships. They often have an ownership stake in the firm.\n\nThese levels and titles can vary based on the specific practice within Deloitte Consulting US and may change over time. Additionally, career progression may involve lateral moves or promotions within different service lines or industries within the firm.",
